 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Associate - Global Technology AI Allianz Global Investors 1,914 reviews San Francisco, CA Allianz Global Investors 1,914 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Allianz Global Investors offers a diversified range of active investment strategies across four main pillars: equities, fixed income, multi asset and alternatives. Our expertise covers the developed and emerging markets as well as public and private markets. At Allianz Global Investors, our people enjoy motivating, fulfilling careers. If you’re looking for a fast-paced working environment, then join us now! We’re committed to giving our people – experienced and energetic professionals alike – the opportunities and experiences they seek to thrive and gain personal fulfilment.
 
We are looking for you! Allianz Global Investors is currently seeking an Associate to join our Global Artificial Intelligence Investment Team covering a variety of strategies including AI, Cloud, Thematic, and Multi-Asset. In this role, you will play an integral role with the team in all aspects of the investment process and assist with the active management of several strategies. The Associate can expect to have meaningful interaction with senior professionals both internally and externally with management teams. The role is based in our San Francisco office, and will consider those outside of the Bay Area with willingness to relocate.
 
 Responsibilities: 
## Generate new investment ideas primarily focused on the technology sector.
 ## Conduct due diligence for potential investments including modelling, interacting with senior management and customers/partners.
 ## Support the management of existing portfolios including daily trading & monitoring, monthly reporting and commentary, fundamental research & financial modeling, and marketing & client support.
 ## Maintain and enhance presentations, whitepapers and marketing collateral related to our thematic innovation strategies.
 ## Active participation in company and sell side analyst meetings, industry conferences, portfolio company discussions and decisions.
 ## Strong interest in technological innovation and the ramifications for public equities/private companies.
 
## BA / BS degree required
 ## Degree major - Economics, or Finance; would also consider Computer Science majors interested in Investment Management
 ## 2-4 years of investment related work experience; Prior experience in equity research, consulting or investment banking a plus
 ## Exceptional writing and verbal communication skills; Strong data management and research skills
 ## A passion for the markets & innovation
 ## Ability to learn quickly & thrive in a fast pace environment
 
